Preconditions:
The input array nums is not null.
The input array nums contains at least one element.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer value representing the minimum deviation of the array.
The minimum deviation is calculated after performing some number of operations on the array.
The array nums may be modified during the operations.
The minimum deviation is the smallest possible difference between the maximum and minimum values in the array after the operations.
The minimum deviation is non-negative.